verses.roman:
durgati nā haya tāra, sad-gati se haya
prabhu-bhaṅgī ei, pāche jānibā niścaya"

synonyms: durgati—a bad result; nā haya tāra—is not his; sat-gati se haya—he must have achieved liberation; prabhu-bhaṅgī—a sport of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; ei—this; pāche—later; jānibā—you will understand; niścaya—the real fact.
translation: "Haridāsa cannot have been degraded; he must have attained liberation. This is a pastime of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu. You will all understand it later."
